{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-717-developing-wireless-carplay-systems"]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC17","title":"Developing Wireless CarPlay Systems","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-717-Developing-Wireless-CarPlay-Systems"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Wireless CarPlay is perfect for any trip. Get in your car without taking your iPhone out of your bag or pocket, and start experiencing CarPlay effortlessly. Learn how to design your CarPlay system to connect wirelessly to iPhone. Understand hardware requirements, best practices for a great user experience, and how to optimize the pairing and reconnection process."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-252-Advances-in-CarPlay-Systems","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-719-Enabling-Your-App-for-CarPlay","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2"]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/717","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (34 min)","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"references":{"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","alt":null},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"title":"WWDC17","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-252-Advances-in-CarPlay-Systems":{"title":"Advances in CarPlay Systems","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay is a smarter, safer way to use your iPhone in the car. Learn how to update your vehicle system to take advantage of new features in iOS 13. Add support for dynamically changing screen sizes, second screens such as instrument clusters, and even irregularly shaped displays. Learn how to support “Hey Siri” for hands-free voice activation."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-252-advances-in-carplay-systems","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-252-Advances-in-CarPlay-Systems"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","alt":null},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2017/717":{"checksum":null,"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/717","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2017\/717"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1":{"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"Developing CarPlay Systems, Part 1","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-722-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-1","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-722-developing-carplay-systems-part-1","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay is a smarter, safer way to use your iPhone in the car. Learn how CarPlay works and how to design your car’s infotainment system to work seamlessly with iPhone. Understand best practices for a great user experience that integrates CarPlay with the car’s native system."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-723-developing-carplay-systems-part-2","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-723-Developing-CarPlay-Systems-Part-2","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Developing CarPlay Systems, Part 2","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how CarPlay integrates with your car’s infotainment system. Understand how CarPlay is designed to work with your car’s resources including the display, speakers, microphone, user inputs, steering wheel controls, instrument cluster and sensors."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-719-Enabling-Your-App-for-CarPlay":{"type":"topic","title":"Enabling Your App for CarPlay","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-719-enabling-your-app-for-carplay","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-719-Enabling-Your-App-for-CarPlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand how to enable your audio, messaging, VoIP calling or automaker app for CarPlay. Audio, messaging and VoIP calling apps use a consistent design that’s optimized for use in the car. Automaker apps provide vehicle specific controls and displays to keep drivers connected without leaving CarPlay. Explore best practices and learn about the tools and frameworks for CarPlay apps."}],"kind":"article"}}}